---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AffiliateLink from '../components/AffiliateLink.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'v0.dev Review: AI Code Generation That Works (2025)',
  description: 'Honest v0.dev review after actually using it. Generates React/Next.js code from prompts. Free and powerful for developers. Not for non-technical users.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['v0.dev review', 'v0 AI code generator', 'v0 vs Cursor', 'Vercel v0', 'AI website builder for developers'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-[#FEF9F3] py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#E07A5F] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        Tested · Honest · No Hype
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        v0.dev Review: AI Code Generation That Works
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        v0.dev generates React/Next.js code from natural language prompts. It's free, powerful, and actually works. But it's for developers, not everyone.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick verdict: v0 is the best free AI code generator for React developers. You get actual code you own, can deploy anywhere, and the quality is surprisingly good. But you need React/Next.js knowledge. If you can't code, this isn't for you.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What v0 Does -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What v0.dev Actually Does
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="text-lg font-black mb-4">You type prompts. v0 generates React/Next.js code.</p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">Simple prompt: "Create a landing page for a coffee shop with hero section, menu, and contact form"</p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">v0 outputs: Complete React component with:</p>

      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-6">
        <li>• Clean, modern code using shadcn/ui components</li>
        <li>• Responsive design (mobile, tablet, desktop)</li>
        <li>• Tailwind CSS styling</li>
        <li>• Proper React patterns and structure</li>
        <li>• Copy and paste into your project</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">The code quality is shockingly good. Not perfect. But definitely usable, especially with light editing.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-6">
      <p class="font-bold mb-2">The catch:</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">v0 is for developers. If you don't know React, you can't use what it generates. You won't know how to run it, deploy it, or customize it. This is a developer tool, not a "website builder" like Wix or Squarespace.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      v0.dev Pricing
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <!-- Free -->
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-4">
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-xl text-gray-900">v0 Free</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600">For individual developers</p>
          </div>
          <span class="bg-green-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-bold">FREE</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <li>✓ Unlimited generations</li>
          <li>✓ All UI components (shadcn/ui)</li>
          <li>✓ React, Next.js, Vue support</li>
          <li>✓ Code export and ownership</li>
          <li>✓ Basic image uploads (for reference)</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="https://v0.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-black py-3 px-6 rounded-lg">
          Start Free
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- Pro (Note: As of my knowledge, v0 is free, but may have paid tiers) -->
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-4">
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-xl text-gray-900">v0 Pro (Future/Possible)</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600">For power users (check v0.dev for current pricing)</p>
          </div>
          <span class="bg-purple-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-bold">Coming Soon</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <li>✓ Higher rate limits</li>
          <li>✓ Advanced features</li>
          <li>✓ Priority generation</li>
          <li>✓ Team collaboration</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">Note: v0 is currently free for most users. Pro tiers may be added in the future.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
      <h3 class="font-black mb-3">Hosting is free (with Vercel)</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700">Generate code with v0, deploy to <AffiliateLink href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</AffiliateLink> free. Vercel's free tier is generous: automatic deployments, global CDN, SSL certificates, custom domains. You can host multiple v0 projects for free.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What I Liked -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What v0 Does Well
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✓ Actually Free (Generously)</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">No credit card required. No rate limits that kill usage (for individuals). Unlimited generations. This is how AI tools should be—free to try, pay only if you need advanced features.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Compare to Cursor ($20/mo), Copilot ($10/mo). v0 is completely free for the core functionality.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✓ High-Quality Code</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">The generated code isn't garbage. It uses:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Modern React patterns (hooks, functional components)</li>
          <li>• shadcn/ui components (beautiful, accessible UI library)</li>
          <li>• Tailwind CSS (industry-standard styling)</li>
          <li>• Proper TypeScript types</li>
          <li>• Responsive design out of the box</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">You could ship this code with light editing. It's not just a starting point—it's 80% done.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✓ You Own the Code</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">v0 generates code. You copy it. It's yours. Do whatever you want with it. Deploy anywhere. Modify however you want. No license restrictions.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Compare to Durable, Framer, Wix where you're locked into their platform. v0 gives you actual code you own.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✓ Iterative Refinement</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Generate initial code. Then refine with prompts: "Make the hero section bigger," "Add testimonials," "Change color scheme to purple." v0 updates the code based on feedback.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">This conversation style development is faster than writing from scratch, especially for boilerplate-heavy features.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✓ Image Upload Support</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Upload screenshots or designs. v0 can analyze them and generate matching code. This is huge for replicating existing designs or building from mockups.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Upload a Figma design → Get React code that matches. Insane productivity booster.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Limitations -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Doesn't Work (Limitations)
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✗ Not for Non-Developers</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">If you can't code, you can't use v0. Period. You'll get code you don't know how to run, deploy, or customize. You need: React knowledge, Next.js understanding, development environment setup, deployment skills.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">This is the biggest limitation. v0 is for developers who want AI assistance, not non-technical users who want websites.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✗ Requires Technical Setup</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">v0 generates code. You need to:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Have Node.js installed</li>
          <li>• Create a Next.js project</li>
          <li>• Install dependencies (npm install)</li>
          <li>• Set up shadcn/ui components</li>
          <li>• Configure Tailwind CSS</li>
          <li>• Deploy to <AffiliateLink href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</AffiliateLink> or similar</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">If this sounds foreign, v0 isn't for you. Use Durable or Framer instead.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✗ Not for Complex Applications</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">v0 excels at UI generation. For complex backend logic, databases, APIs, it's limited. You can generate simple CRUD, but full-stack apps require manual coding.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Great for: Landing pages, marketing sites, dashboards, simple tools. Not for: Complex SaaS products, apps with intricate business logic.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✗ No Visual Editor</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">v0 is prompt-based. No drag-and-drop visual editor. If you want visual design control, use Framer or Webflow. If you're comfortable with code and prompts, v0 is faster.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">The tradeoff: Speed and code ownership vs. visual control. Choose based on your workflow.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who Should Use v0 -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Should You Use v0?
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Use v0 if:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• You know React and Next.js</li>
          <li>• You want code you own and control</li>
          <li>• You're comfortable with development environments</li>
          <li>• You want to accelerate UI development</li>
          <li>• You don't mind light code editing</li>
          <li>• Free hosting on <AffiliateLink href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</AffiliateLink> appeals to you</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">❌ Don't use v0 if:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• You don't know how to code</li>
          <li>• You want visual drag-and-drop editing</li>
          <li>• You need a simple website fast with zero technical work</li>
          <li>• You're building complex applications (not just UI)</li>
          <li>• You don't want to touch code at all</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      v0 vs Alternatives
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="p-4 border font-bold">Feature</th>
            <th class="p-4 border font-bold">v0.dev</th>
            <th class="p-4 border font-bold"><a href="/deals/cursor" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Cursor</a></th>
            <th class="p-4 border font-bold"><a href="/durable-ai-review" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Durable</a></th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-4 border">Price</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Free</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">$20/mo</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">$15-30/mo</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 border">Code Ownership</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">✓ Yes</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">✓ Yes</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">❌ No</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-4 border">Technical Skill</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">High</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Medium</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">None</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 border">Best For</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Developers</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Developers</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Everyone else</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How to Use v0 Effectively -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      How to Use v0 Effectively
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="text-lg font-black mb-4">v0 is a tool, not magic. Best practices:</p>

      <ol class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>Start specific:</strong> "Create a landing page for coffee shop with hero, menu, contact form" beats "Create a website"</li>

        <li><strong>Iterate gradually:</strong> Generate base version first. Then refine with specific prompts. Don't ask for everything at once.</li>

        <li><strong>Upload references:</strong> Upload screenshots of designs you like. v0 can match the style and layout.</li>

        <li><strong>Edit the code:</strong> v0 gets you 80% there. Light editing is faster than endless regeneration.</li>

        <li><strong>Use shadcn/ui:</strong> v0 generates shadcn/ui components. Learn the library for easier customization.</li>

        <li><strong>Deploy to Vercel:</strong> Free hosting, automatic deployments, global CDN. Perfect companion for v0 projects.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom Line -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-6">The Bottom Line</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">v0 is the best free AI code generator for React developers. The quality is impressive, the price is unbeatable (free), and you own what you create.</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">But it's not for everyone:</p>

      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-6">
        <li>• <strong>Need React skills</strong> — This is a developer tool, not a website builder</li>
        <li>• <strong>Requires setup</strong> — Development environment, deployment, technical know-how</li>
        <li>• <strong>Not for complex apps</strong> — Great for UI, limited for backend logic</li>
        <li>• <strong>No visual editor</strong> — Code and prompts, not drag-and-drop</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">If you're a developer who knows React/Next.js: v0 is a no-brainer. Free, powerful, generates usable code. Start using it today.</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">If you're non-technical: Use <a href="/durable-ai-review" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Durable</a> or <a href="/durable-vs-v0-vs-framer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Framer</a>. v0 will only frustrate you.</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">The right tool for the right user. v0 fills its niche perfectly: free AI code generation for React developers. Nothing else comes close at this price point.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Related AI Builder Guides
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/durable-vs-v0-vs-framer" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Durable vs v0 vs Framer</h3>
